		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />That's cool. Hope you do something fun with it. If nothing else, this kind of thing does make a good live demonstration, like how ConnectedNES was used to show tweets live, gets people to interact with it a little. Maybe if we had a popular enough peripheral to get a standard started we could start getting a game library that supports it. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> Maybe even just a Chess or Go client for an existing online network would be fun to try.

		

