	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I happen to prefer wired network connections.<br /><br />Still, if you can connect to the internet (wired or wirelessly), a network diagnostics program can be made up (and then you can test its working) and a gopher client program can also be made up. And then, you can make up games such as mahjong or poker or bridge (I am naming these games specifically because they involve hidden information, rather than chess and Go which do not involve hidden information and so do not required to have separate displays for each player), which may use their own protocols.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


